Step 1. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin using the income statement values.  
 • Gross Profit = 4788736.33  
 • Total Revenue = 16388736.33  
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (4788736.33 / 16388736.33) × 100  
  ≈ 29.20%

Step 2. Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio using the cash flow and balance sheet details.  
 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from cash flow statement) = -6316405.44  
 • Total Current Liabilities (from balance sheet; sum of Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable) = 4319436.82  
 • Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = -6316405.44 / 4319436.82  
  ≈ -1.46

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "29.20%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-1.46"
  }
}
